.jpg" alt="Barbie Ryan Gosling Margot Robbie" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_boat_Margot_Robbie.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_boat_Margot_Robbie-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_boat_Margot_Robbie-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_boat_Margot_Robbie-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_boat_Margot_Robbie-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_boat_Margot_Robbie-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3470022" class="wp-caption-text"> Barbie and Ken take a boat ride to the “real world”. CREDIT: Warner Bros.</figcaption></figure><p> <em>Barbie</em> , starring Margot Robbie and Ryan Gosling, has become the highest-grossing film of 2023, crossing the $1.4billion mark at the global box office.</p><p> As a result of the film&#39;s success, Mattel is planning a slew of movie projects based on the company&#39;s IP, including Polly Pocket by Lena Dunham, a <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/film-fans-react-to-news-that-jj-abrams-is-making-a-hot-wheels-movie-3465278">Hot Wheels film from JJ Abrams</a> , and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/daniel-kaluuya-barney-film-reportedly-surrealistic-for-adults-3464936">Barney starring Daniel Kaluuya</a> .</p><p> “What you saw around the <em>Barbie</em> movie was, we believe, a template, a case study, an opportunity to truly understand the value and appeal that our brands have, the cultural resonance, and, importantly, our ability to execute these projects both creatively and commercially,” Mattel CEO, Ynon Kreiz, said. “We hope and expect to have more. I&#39;m not saying it will be as big or as successful as <em>Barbie</em> , but it will be the same approach.”</p><p> Mattel expects continued profits from <em>Barbie</em> into 2024 and beyond. The film is set to hit streaming services on Tuesday (September 12).</p><p> In a<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/barbie-review-margot-robbie-ryan-gosling-3470019">four-star review</a> , <em>NME</em> wrote: “What follows is a nuanced, rose-tinted comedy adventure, set to a stonking pop soundtrack featuring <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lizzo">Lizzo</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/billie-eilish">Billie Eilish</a> , that somehow lives up to the immense hype. To borrow a pun from Ken&#39;s coolest jacket (out of a long lineup), <em>Barbie</em> is more than &#39;kenough&#39;.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/heres-how-much-mattel-earn-barbie-in-2023-3496059">Here&#39;s how much Mattel will earn from &#39;Barbie&#39; in 2023</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
